0crisis%20and%20could%20put%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDiane%20Shelton%2C%2058%2C%20has%20been%20working%20as%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%20for%20over%2025%20years%20%E2%80%94%20but%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-debt-social-security-gen-x-retirement-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudent%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20still%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-gen-x-degree-better-retirement-income-driven-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20figures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShelton's%20debt%20load%20is%20something%20of%20a%20double-edged%20sword.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20no%20doubt%20the%20value%20of%20the%20education%20and%20the%20value%20and%20the%20intrinsic%20richness%20that%20I%20have%20from%20the%20work%20that%20I've%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20that's%20coupled%20with%20a%20heavy%20loan%20burden%2C%20complicated%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20the%20interest%20it's%20accruing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20taken%20forbearances%20at%20times%20when%20I%20really%20couldn't%20afford%20my%20mortgage.%20I%20had%20to%20pick%20and%20choose%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Even%20now%2C%20with%20a%20stable%20and%20well-paying%20career%2C%20her%20debt%20is%20still%20impacting%20her%20economic%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20a%20bit%20different%20for%20Larry%2C%2075%2C%20who%20requested%20his%20last%20name%20be%20withheld%20for%20privacy.%20He's%20staring%20down%20a%20%24208%2C000%20balance%20that%20he%20took%20out%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20to%20help%20his%20kids%20go%20to%20school.%20While%20they%20took%20out%20federal%20student%20loans%20for%20themselves%2C%20Larry%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20their%20options%20weren't%20limited.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESo%20he%20took%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparent-