f%20from%20my%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20later%2C%20my%20husband%20left%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20add%20to%20the%20shock%2C%20I%20found%20out%20weeks%20later%20that%20I%20was%20pregnant.%20We'd%20been%20trying%20for%20children%20for%20a%20few%20years%20and%20had%20unfortunately%20suffered%20two%20miscarriages%20in%20our%20fertility%20journey%2C%20so%20finding%20out%20I%20was%20pregnant%20was%20a%20piece%20of%20joy%20amid%20a%20very%20trying%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20pregnancy%20was%20surprisingly%20calm.%20I%20tried%20applying%20for%20a%20few%20jobs%20but%20soon%20gave%20up%2C%20as%20sleep%20deprivation%20left%20my%20energy%20levels%20on%20the%20floor.%20I%20gave%20in%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20leaning%20on%20some%20of%20my%20savings%20and%20taking%20statutory%20maternity%20pay%20during%20the%20pregnancy%20and%20the%20first%20year%20of%20my%20daughter's%20life%20while%20continuing%20to%20do%20some%20volunteer%20mentoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20struggle%20came%20after%20my%20daughter%20was%20born%2C%20as%20I%20tried%20to%20navigate%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parent-loneliness-no-partner-202404%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20only%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20family%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20registered%20with%20the%20job%20center%20in%20mid-2022%20when%20my%20daughter%20turned%2018%20months%20old.%20I%20needed%20to%20return%20to%20a%20career%20for%20financial%20reasons%20and%20to%20boost%20my%20self-esteem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20center%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EConnecting%20Communities%20scheme%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhere%20I%20could%20receive%20%C2%A3500%20(%24640)%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etoward%20a%20chosen%20training%20course.%20That's%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20something%20completely%20different%3A%20retrain%20as%20a%20plumber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20weeks%20of%20applying%2