quot%3BI%20always%20felt%20like%20a%20failure%2C%20like%20I%20should%20be%20providing%20for%20my%20kids%20the%20way%20I%20was%20provided%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20never%20able%20to%20do%20that.%20I%20was%20just%20trying%20to%20make%20it%20to%20the%20next%20paycheck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae75898b-cd85-4b44-9bb5-9c0fb5858f2d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20back%20on%20her%20feet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20stroke%20of%20luck%2C%20she%20got%20the%20opportunity%20to%20teach%20sociology%20courses%20at%20a%20community%20college%2C%20which%20paid%20her%20%2434%2C000%20a%20year%20in%202006.%20Her%20salary%20rose%20to%20%2456%2C000%20a%20few%20years%20later.%20Having%20plenty%20of%20vacations%20and%20more%20stable%20hours%20allowed%20her%20to%20be%20more%20present%20in%20her%20kids'%20lives%2C%20though%20money%20was%20still%20a%20stressor.%20She%20made%20extra%20income%20from%20advising%20campus%20clubs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20kept%20the%20wheels%20on%20the%20bus%2C%20but%20we%20never%20got%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20barely%20had%20money%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-peak-boomer-alice-social-security-masters-degree-student-loans-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hadn't%20invested%20much%20for%20her%20kids'%20futures.%20All%20she%20could%20think%20about%20was%20squeezing%20enough%20money%20out%20of%20her%20next%20paycheck%20to%20take%20her%20kids%20to%20a%20museum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20honestly%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20life%20not%20caring%20about%20money%20unless%20I%20had%20an%20emergency%20expense%20and%20I%20couldn't%20pay%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20money%20was%20probably%20something%20that%20corrupted%20people%2C%20and%20I%20just%20didn't%20have%20a%20very%20positive%20opinion%20of%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20second%20husband%2C%20whom%20she%20met%20in%202015%20and%20married%20in%202021%2C%20had%20maxed%20out%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retiree-saved-too-much-in-401k-financial-independence-strategy-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20saved%20much%20of%20his%20income.%20They%20agreed%20she%20would%20take%20off%20a%20few%20months%20to%20write%20children's%20books%20and%20see%20if%20it%20was%20financially%20sustainable.%20Once%20it%20became%20clear%20this%20career%20switch%20wasn't%20viable%2C%20she%20began%20investing%20after%20her%20husband%20convinced%20her%20she%20would%20be%20good%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20pushed%20back%20because%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20was%20rewarding.%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20would%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20contributing%20to%20society%20in%20a%20meaningful%20way%20as%20an%20investor%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b80f0754-8266-413d-a72e-4ce1c1c3c4c5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReaching%20financial%20independence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20sold%20her%20car%20and%20invested%20that%20money%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20starting%20with%20buying%20a%20share%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%2C%20then%20diversifying%20her%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20realizations%20for%20me%20is%20that%20I%20used%20to%20think%20you%20needed%20more%20money%20to%20be%20wealthy%2C%20but%20now%20what%20I've%20learned%20is%20you%20can%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20and%20still%20live%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20make%20a%20very%20small%20amount%20of%20income%20and%20live%20within%20your%20means%20and%20live%20stress-free%20and%20happy%20and%20build%20wealth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20knew%20she%20couldn't%20start%20her%20financial%20independence%20journey%20alone%2C%20and%20her%20more%20financially%20savvy%20husband%20helped%20her%20get%20on%20track.%20On%20a%20national%20parks%20trip%2C%20they%20decided%20they%20would%20do%20whatever%20they%20could%20to%20retire%20early%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20exploring%20the%20world%20without%20worrying%20about%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20read%20dozens%20of%20books%20and%20articles%20about%20financial%20markets%2C%20completed%20graduate%20degrees%20in%20financial%20planning%2C%20and%20became%20a%20Certified%20Financial%20Behavior%20Specialist.%20She%20modified%20her%20investing%20strategies%20to%20fit%20her%20personality%2C%20schedule%2C%20and%20risk%20tolerance.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20started%20with%20%24240%2C000%20invested%20in%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20about%20%2480%2C000%20in%20equity.%20Within%20the%20first%20four%20years%2C%20they%20doubled%20their%20investments%20twice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20mid-40s%2C%20she%20paid%20off%20her%20student%20debt%2C%20which%20she%20considered%20a%20huge%20milestone.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20she%20could%20start%20saving%20money%20and%20max%20out%20her%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20husband%20adopted%20a%20minimalist%20lifestyle%2C%20starting%20by%20adopting%20a%20%26quot%3Bone%20in%2C%20one%20out%26quot%3B%20rule%20%E2%80%94%20for%20every%20shirt%20she%20bought%2C%20she%20would%20sell%20one.%20They%20prioritized%20experiences%20over%20gifts%20and%20significantly%20increased%20savings%2C%20only%20purchasing%20what%20they%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20she%20estimates%20they've%20saved%20over%2040%25%20of%20their%20income%20%E2%80%94%20and%20about%2060%25%20if%20including%20investments%20from%20home%20sales.%20Still%2C%20she%20said%20they're%20not%20overly%20frugal%20and%20spend%20on%20fitness%2C%20food%2C%20and%20hobbies%20like%20bikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20created%20an%20%26quot%3Bintense%20and%20intimidating%26quot%3B%20spreadsheet%20to%20track%20everything%20coming%20in%20and%20going%20out.%20She%20added%20sections%20for%20emergency%20savings%2C%20investments%2C%20net%20worth%2C%20and%20their%20%26quot%3Bslush%20fund%26quot%3B%20of%20purchases%20above%20%24500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20pivoted%20to%20moving%2020%25%20of%20her%20husband's%20base%20income%2C%20100%25%20of%20her%20income%2C%20and%20at%20least%2050%25%20of%20bonuses%20into%20investments.%20Her%20husband's%20military%20pension%2C%20which%20is%20inflation-adjusted%2C%20has%20also%20taken%20some%20weight%20off%20the%20planning%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20paying%20ourselves%20first%2C%20we've%20adopted%20the%20'give%20every%20dollar%20a%20job'%20approach.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20each%20month%2C%20any%20'extra%20money'%20is%20assigned%20to%20either%20slush%2C%20emergency%2C%20or%20it's%20invested%2C%26quot%3B%20Dove%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDove%20didn't%20want%20to%20work%20even%20more%20hours%2C%20which%20would%20force%20her%20to%20sacrifice%20time%20with%20her%20kids%2C%20so%20she%20made%20more%20with%20less.%20They%20recently%20bought%20a%20home%20for%20%2496%2C000%20in%20Bloomington%2C%20Illinois%2C%20just%20as%20State%20Farm%20moved%20their%20headquarters%20and%20home%20prices%20fell%2C%20then%20sold%20their%20house%20right%20as%20Rivian%20came%20in%20and%20prices%20rose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20encouraged%20her%20to%20dabble%20in%20real%20estate%20investing%2C%20putting%20their%20mountain%20home%20up%20on%20Airbnb.%20The%20home%20was%20almost%20immediately%20booked%20out%20each%20week%20for%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDove%20has%20published%20four%20children's%20picture%20books%20and%20spends%20her%20days%20writing%2C%20facilitating%20workshops%2C%20and%20working%20as%20a%20financial%20coach.%20She%20is%20also%20an%20angel%20investor%20in%20some%20startups.%20Ultimately%2C%20she%20hopes%20to%20retire%20early%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20loved%20ones%20and%20set%20them%20up%20for%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20we%20have%20not%20hit%20our%20FI%20number%20yet%2C%20we%