t%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20youngest%20millennials%20are%2028%20and%2029%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20cusper%20Zillennials%20are%20twice%20as%20wealthy%20as%20their%20geriatric%20millennial%20peers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20of%20them%20are%20living%20at%20home%20and%20staying%20single%20longer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20writing%20about%20millennials%20since%202018%20when%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F01%2F17%2Fwhere-millennials-end-and-generation-z-begins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E22%20to%2037%20years%20old%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Entering%20adulthood%20during%20the%20rise%20of%20social%20media%20and%20online%20shopping%2C%20coupled%20with%20some%20unique%20economic%20challenges%2C%20put%20this%20cohort%20in%20the%20limelight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20were%20fascinated%20by%20what%20the%20kids%20were%20up%20to.%20The%20millennial%20stereotypes%20of%20brunching%20on%20avocado%20toast%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmillennials-rely-on-parents-money-housing-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20with%20their%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20longer%20had%20the%20world%20especially%20intrigued%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20this%20generation%20that%20seemingly%20couldn't%20grow%20up%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20they%20have%20grown%20up.%20The%20eldest%20millennials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypical-40-year-old-oldest-millennials-debt-net-worth-earnings-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturn%2043%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Ffact-tank%2F2019%2F01%2F17%2Fwhere-millennials-end-and-generation-z-begins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20Research%20Center's%20definition%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20generation%20has%20entered%20peak%20milestone%20years%20of%20homebuying%20and%20starting%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20the%20generation%20will%20age%20out%20of%20their%2020s%20entirely%20and%20leave%20young%20adulthood%20behind.%20The%20youngest%20of%20the%20generation%2C%20born%20in%201995%20and%201996%2C%20turn%2028%20and%2029%20this%20year%2C%20and%20just%20under%209%20million%2020-something%20millennials%20remain%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Fpopest%2F2020s-national-detail.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20US%20Census%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20cohort%20falls%20into%20cusper%20territory%2C%20those%20born%20between%20generations%2C%20and%20are%20part%20of%20the%20larger%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotting-zillennials-millenial-gen-z-tiktok-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZillennial%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20microgeneration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20quite%20millennial%2C%20not%20quite%20Gen%20Z%2C%20these%20late%2020-somethings%20are%20shaped%20by%20the%20pandemic%20happening%20early%20on%20in%20their%20careers%20and%20initial%20wealth-building%20years.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20they're%20actually%20faring%20better%20than%20their%20older%20millennial%20peers%2C%20and%20their%20struggles%20point%20to%20larger%20cracks%20in%20America's%20social%20support%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227edd6569-b00b-494c-ac42-72ec8eefba36%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20bridge%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDiana%20Elliott%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20programs%20at%20Population%20Reference%20Bureau%20(PRB)%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20one's%20late%2020s%20have%20always%20been%20peak%20years%20to%20establish%20careers.%20However%2C%20these%20particular%20late%2020-somethings%20saw%20the%20pandemic%20shorten%20their%20typical%20in-office%20experience%20more%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20generation.%20They%20were%20only%2024%20and%2025%20at%20the%20time%2C%20in%20the%20workforce%20for%20just%20a%20few%20years%2C%20and%20they%20fear%20it%20gave%20them%20an%20uneven%20footing%20in%20the%20labor%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20feel%20this%20has%20negatively%20affected%20their%20ability%20to%20learn%20the%20soft%20skills%20that%20come%20from%20working%20in%20an%20office%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20missing%20out%20on%20growth%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabby%20Davis%2C%20a%20career%20expert%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indeed.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndeed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20younger%20millennial%20herself%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20But%20Davis%20said%20Indeed%20research%20shows%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20back%20into%20an%20office%20full-time.%20While%20return-to-office%20mandates%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20push%20them%20away%2C%20she%20says%20the%20youngest%20millennials%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20stick%20around%20in%20a%20job%20than%20Gen%20Z%2C%20who%20view%20their%20jobs%20with%20more%20dispensability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuspers%20often%20act%20as%20a%20bridge%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20but%20younger%20millennials%20may%20find%20it%20challenging%20to%20bridge%20this%20generational%20gap%20when%20reporting%20to%20older%20colleagues%20and%20managing%20younger%20ones%2C%20Davis%20said.%20But%20they've%20already%20pushed%20for%20greater%20flexibility%2C%20communication%2C%20and%20transparency%20at%20work%2C%20which%20she%20thinks%20can%20help%20them%20ease%20that%20transition.%20Millennials%2C%20now%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2020%2F04%2F28%2Fmillennials-overtake-baby-boomers-as-americas-largest-generation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20move%20into%20leadership%20roles%20as%20they%20age%20into%20their%2030s%20and%2040s%20which%20Davis%20believes%20will%20help%20%26quot%3Bfoster%20diversity%2C%20accountability%2C%20and%20more%20meaningful%20workplaces.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20generation%20ages%2C%20Elliott%20predicts%20they'll%20start%20taking%20over%20boomers'%20roles%20as%20they%20retire.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20exits%20from%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20not%20just%20now%20but%20into%20the%20next%20decade%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20could%20be%20a%20really%20interesting%20time%20for%20opportunities%20for%20young%20millennials%20in%20the%20labor%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228157dcf1-280c-4073-80a1-e4aa7cceef67%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERollin'%20in%20the%20dough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20glance%2C%20it%20seemed%20the%20pandemic%20might%20also%20jeopardize%20the%20wealth%20trajectory%20of%20the%20youngest%20millennials%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-class-of-2020-a-look-at-gen-z-as-it-graduates-into-chaos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoldest%20Gen%20Zers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Older%20millennials%20struggled%20with%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%20and%202008%20financial%20crisis%2C%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20and%20%241.2%20trillion%20in%20student%20loan%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20St.%20Louis%20Fed%20predicted%20that%20those%20born%20in%20the%201980s%20were%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F1980s-millennials-wealth-the-great-recession-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20came%20to%20wealth%20accumulation.%20Fortunately%2C%20that%20didn't%20come%20to%20pass%3A%20By%202022%2C%20their%20wealth%20levels%20were%2037%25%20above%20expectations.%20But%20the%20wealth%20of%20younger%20millennials%20and%20older%20Gen%20Zers%20made%20an%20even%20sharper%20swing%20at%2039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20wealth%20is%20even%20more%20striking%20when%20compared%20to%20their%20older%20peers%20at%20the%20same%20age.%20In%202013%2C%2024-%20to%2033-year-olds%20had%20a%20typical%20wealth%20level%20of%20%2416%2C567%2C%20per%20data%20the%20St.%20Louis%20Fed%20provided%20Business%20Insider.%20That's%20more%20than%20doubled%20(even%20accounting%20for%20inflation)%20for%20those%20aged%2026%20to%2032%20in%202022%2C%20who%20have%20a%20typical%20wealth%20level%20of%20%2455%2C760.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20shows%20how%20much%20the%20macroeconomic%20context%20can%20change%20even%20within%20a%20generation.%20St.%20Louis%20Fed%20data%20scientist%20Lowell%20Ricketts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20at%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20these%20older%20millennials%20still%20grappling%20with%20some%20of%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20a%20subdued%20economy%20in%20which%20employment%20outcomes%20languish%20for%20some%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYounger%20millennials%20have%20made%20it%20by%202022%20through%20much%20of%20the%20pandemic%20disruptions%20and%20found%20themselves%20with%20a%20much%20higher%20amount%20of%20wealth%20accumulated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERicketts%20said%20the%20coronavirus%20recession's%20shorter%20duration%20and%20more%20aggressive%20federal%20policy%20response%20saved%20them.%20A%20government%20cash%20infusion%20and%20a%20lockdown%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenrys-millennials-pandemic-reopening-financial-challenges-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevented%20us%20from%20spending%20on%20trips%20and%20dinners%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bbuoyed%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20outcomes%20across%20the%20wealth%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20making%202022%20an%20overall%20high-water%20mark%20for%20wealth%20accumulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b639908-5cdb-46ab-a460-2f9c4335c4e3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreatively%20becoming%20homeowners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20finds%20that%20real%20estate%20was%20a%20primary%20driver%20for%20younger%20millennials'%20wealth%20gains%2C%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-forecast-millennials-buying-homes-crisis-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehot%20pandemic%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20hiked%20up%20home%20values.%20But%20aren't%20millennials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-homebuyer-challenges-starter-home-shortage-millennials-gen-z-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunable%20to%20buy%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20those%20who've%20had%20less%20time%20to%20save%3F%20Ricketts%20said%20that%20despite%20affordability%20issues%2C%20some%20have%20managed%20to%20make%20it%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20millennials%20are%20getting%20creative%20about%20becoming%20homeowners%2C%20explained%20Jessica%20Lautz%2C%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20at%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors.%20They're%20living%20at%20home%20first%20to%20save%20money%20or%20partnering%20up%20%E2%80%94%2019%25%20of%20those%20aged%2025%20to%2033%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20youngest%20millennials%2C%20are%20unmarried%20couples%2C%20the%20highest%20NAR%20sees%20among%20any%20generation%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fresearch-and-statistics%2Fresearch-reports%2Fhome-buyer-and-seller-generational-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenerational%20Trends%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20also%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20get%20down%20payment%20transfers%2C%20often%20from%20family%20members%20helping%20out%20with%20the%20purchase.%20Maybe%20that's%20why%2055%25%20of%20them%20prefer%20to%20live%20near%20friends%20and%20family%3B%20the%20only%20other%20generation%20that%20comes%20close%20to%20this%20preference%20