0as%20housing%20affordability%2C%20getting%20a%20foothold%20in%20the%20work%20world%2C%20and%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20generations%20are%20nuanced.%20Not%20everyone%20is%20faring%20well%3B%20some%20millennials%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-typical-alice-middle-class-poverty-housing-food-benefits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estuck%20in%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20young%20millennial%20women%20have%20lost%20ground%20in%20terms%20of%20health%20and%20safety.%20%26quot%3BSystems%20and%20supports%20are%20not%20in%20place%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20best%20help%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Elliott%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20that%20right%20now.%20In%20terms%20of%20maternal%20mortality%2C%20it%20reflects%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20U.S.%20does%20not%20do%20as%20well%20as%20its%20peer%20countries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20some%20of%20younger%20millennials'%20accumulated%20wealth%20has%20faded%20thanks%20to%20inflation%2C%20Ricketts%20said.%20Still%2C%20he's%20hopeful%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20wealth%20outcomes%20we%20see%20in%202022%20might%20be%20an%20optimistic%20note%20and%20a%20source%20of%20strength%20going%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20younger%20millennials%20who%20invest%20their%20wealth%20well%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20consume%20and%20drive%20economic%20growth.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20entrepreneurial%20aspirations%20while%20having%20wealth%20on%20hand%20lets%20you%20pursue%20those%20dreams%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20So%2C%20by%20investing%20in%20oneself%20and%20one's%20passions%2C%20this%20can%20benefit%20the%20broader%20economy%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoungest-millennials-ages-wealth-work-homeownership-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719048422000%2C%22v